    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fossiliferous limestone composed of coral and shell and oolite particles or debris from erosion of older limestones. Calcarenites have been used as a building and ornamental stone, especially in the Apulia region of South Eastern Italy. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
